llm_calls.prompt:
You are a test engineer analyzing an MCP tool to suggest test strategies.

Tool Name: get_dataset_info
Description: Get dataset metadata by ID or UUID.

Returns columns, metrics, and schema details.

IMPORTANT FOR LLM CLIENTS:
- Use numeric ID (e.g., 123) or UUID string (e.g., "a1b2c3d4-...")
- DO NOT use schema.table_name format (e.g., "public.customers")
- To find a dataset ID, use the list_datasets tool first

Example usage:
```json
{
    "identifier": 123
}
```

Or with UUID:
```json
{
    "identifier": "a1b2c3d4-5678-90ab-cdef-1234567890ab"
}
```
Schema: {
  "$defs": {
    "GetDatasetInfoRequest": {
      "description": "Request schema for get_dataset_info with support for ID or UUID.",
      "properties": {
        "use_cache": {
          "default": true,
          "description": "Whether to use Superset's cache layers. When True, will serve from cache if available (query results, metadata, form data). When False, will bypass cache and fetch fresh data.",
          "title": "Use Cache",
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "force_refresh": {
          "default": false,
          "description": "Whether to force refresh cached data. When True, will invalidate existing cache entries and fetch fresh data, then update the cache. Overrides use_cache=True if both are specified.",
          "title": "Force Refresh",
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "refresh_metadata": {
          "default": false,
          "description": "Whether to refresh metadata cache for datasets, tables, and columns. Useful when database schema has changed and you need fresh metadata.",
          "title": "Refresh Metadata",
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "identifier": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            {
              "type": "string"
            }
          ],
          "description": "Dataset identifier - can be numeric ID or UUID string",
          "title": "Identifier"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "identifier"
      ],
      "title": "GetDatasetInfoRequest",
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
  "properties": {
    "request": {
      "anyOf": [
        {
          "type": "string"
        },
        {
          "$ref": "#/$defs/GetDatasetInfoRequest"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Request"
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "request"
  ],
  "type": "object"
}

Analyze this tool and suggest:
1. What are the key scenarios to test? (e.g., valid inputs, edge cases, error conditions)
2. What parameters should be varied in tests?
3. What are potential failure modes?
4. What outputs should be validated?

Respond with a structured analysis in JSON format:
{
  "test_scenarios": [
    {"name": "scenario name", "description": "what to test", "priority": "high|medium|low"}
  ],
  "key_parameters": ["param1", "param2"],
  "edge_cases": ["edge case 1", "edge case 2"],
  "validation_points": ["what to check in output"]
}

